SIMPLE: astronomer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Astronomer
<hw>As*tron"o*mer</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Astronomy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An astrologer.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who is versed in astronomy; one who has a
knowledge of the laws of the heavenly orbs, or the principles by which
their motions are regulated, with their various phenomena.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An undevout <qex>astronomer</qex> is mad.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Astronomian</ent>⟦br⟧
